# ── Keycloak embedded JARs (quay.io/keycloak/keycloak:26.6.3) ────────────────
# KC 26.6.3 ships netty 4.1.133.Final (bumped from 4.1.132 in 26.6.2); the entries
# below require 4.1.135. The 26.6.3 upgrade also resolved & removed all openjdk CVEs
# (CVE-2025-30749/50059/50106/64720/65018, CVE-2026-21945/34282), libcap CVE-2026-4878,
# sqlite CVE-2025-6965, and the netty 4.1.133 CVEs (CVE-2026-42577/42579/42583/42584/42587).
# Verified by a Trivy 0.70.0 scan of the 26.6.3 image.
CVE-2026-44893  # HIGH | netty-codec-haproxy: HAProxy SSL TLV parsing leaks retained slice — KC 26.6.3 ships 4.1.133; fix requires 4.1.135 | Added: 2026-06-09 | Review: 2026-06-23
CVE-2026-44249  # HIGH | netty-handler: IPv6 subnet filter bypass via incorrect comparator masking — KC 26.6.3 ships 4.1.133; fix requires 4.1.135 | Added: 2026-06-09 | Review: 2026-06-23
CVE-2026-45416  # HIGH | netty-handler: SNI handler pre-allocates up to 16 MiB from nine attacker bytes — KC 26.6.3 ships 4.1.133; fix requires 4.1.135 | Added: 2026-06-09 | Review: 2026-06-23
CVE-2026-45674  # HIGH | netty-resolver-dns: DNS cache poisoning via missing bailiwick checks in CNAME — KC 26.6.3 ships 4.1.133; fix requires 4.1.135 | Added: 2026-06-09 | Review: 2026-06-23
CVE-2026-47691  # HIGH | netty-resolver-dns: insufficient bailiwick validation for NS records — KC 26.6.3 ships 4.1.133; fix requires 4.1.135 | Added: 2026-06-09 | Review: 2026-06-23
CVE-2026-48059  # HIGH | netty-codec-haproxy: DoS via memory exhaustion in PROXY protocol v2 codec — KC 26.6.3 ships 4.1.133; fix requires 4.1.135 | Added: 2026-06-14 | Review: 2026-06-21
CVE-2026-50010  # HIGH | netty-handler: improper trust manager handling leads to hostname verification bypass — KC 26.6.3 ships 4.1.133; fix requires 4.1.135 | Added: 2026-06-16 | Review: 2026-06-30

